    <h2 class="heading-s"> Funding for training to teach modern languages </h2>

    <p>To train to be a modern languages teacher, you'll need to do a teacher training course. </p>
<p>Tax-free scholarships of £27,000 are available for <a href="https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/funding-and-support/scholarships-and-bursaries?funding_widget%5Bsubject%5D=languages&button=#funding-widget">eligible trainee French, German, and Spanish languages teachers</a>. </p>
<p>Tax-free bursaries of £25,000 are available for <a href="https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/funding-and-support/scholarships-and-bursaries?funding_widget%5Bsubject%5D=languages&button=#funding-widget">all eligible trainee language teachers, including ancient languages</a>. </p>

  <p>You can receive this alongside a tuition fee and maintenance loan. </p>

  <p>You may also be able to get extra funding support if you are: </p>
  <ul>
<li>a parent or carer </li>
<li>disabled </li>
</ul>
<p>Non-UK citizens without indefinite leave to remain in the UK are unlikely to be eligible for funding. </p>

    <h2 class="heading-s">Check your qualifications</h2>

   <p> You'll need a bachelors degree before training to teach, but it does not have to be in [subject]. </p>
<p>Besides [subject], the most popular degrees people have before doing a teacher training course in [subject] are: </p>

<ul>
  <li>translation studies</li>
<li>english language and literature</li>
<li>psychology</li>
</ul>
 

<p>To train to teach in primary and secondary schools in England, you’ll need: </p>
<ul>
<li>GCSEs at grade 4 (C) or above in English and maths (and science if you want to teach primary) </li>
<li>a bachelor’s degree in any subject </li>
</ul>

 <p>Your training provider may need you to brush up on your computing knowledge before you become a computing teacher. You can do a <a href="https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/how-to-apply-for-teacher-training/subject-knowledge-enhancement">subject knowledge enhancement (SKE)</a> course before you start your teacher training to top up your subject knowledge. </p>

<p><a href="https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/is-teaching-right-for-me/qualifications-you-need-to-teach">Find out more about the qualifications needed to teach</a>.</p> 

 
    <h2 class="heading-s">Paid internship </h2>

<p>If you’re currently doing an undergraduate or master's degree and are interested in teaching computing, you could apply for a <a href="https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/is-teaching-right-for-me/teaching-internship-providers">paid teaching internship</a>. </p>

<p>The 3-week programme could help you to understand what it’s really like in the classroom and get a feel for school life. </p>

<p>You can also find out what it's like to be in a classroom through <a href="https://getintoteaching.education.gov.uk/is-teaching-right-for-me/get-school-experience">unpaid school experience</a>. </p>
